斬新
ざんしん【斬新】 ﾛｰﾏ(zanshin)
〜な novel; original; innovative; unconventional; daring.
▲斬新な意匠[デザイン]　a novel design
・斬新なスタイル　an ⌐original [innovative] style
・斬新な教授法　an innovative method of teaching
・斬新な切り口　〔評論や小説などで〕 an ⌐original [innovative] critical approach.
▲この本の表紙のデザインは斬新な感じがする.　This book's cover design evokes a feeling of novelty.
・60 年代のファッションが, 年輩者にはなつかしく, 若い人には斬新に見える.　To older people the fashions of the sixties are nostalgic, while to young people they seem novel.
斬新さ　novelty; originality.
▲その作品は発想の斬新さが買われて一席になった.　That work won top ⌐prize [honors] because of the novelty of its conception.
